args: Mwah ha ha! Stop your running,\nmy good Pipple!
Oh gosh, oh jeez! I've got a relic on\nthe rampage here! It's gone berserk!
So much for the weapon I was\ncommissioned to make...
We've got to dry it off, quickly!\nHere, we'll help you.
She's gotta be a qilin, right?\nAnd a rokkan...
Er, Grimnir? What are you mumbling about\nthere?
Indeed I am. May I ask why you're\nshouting that fact at me?
Oh, sorry. Just noting that this castle\nreally is home to all kinds of people.
True. We've gathered across the borders of\nrace or nationality because we share a set\nof ideals. Now we work to realize them.
I believe they were all drawn here by\n{player_name}'s welcoming and\nopen-minded nature.
Sorry, what? What are we talking about?
Just that the reason we're all able to live\nhere so happily is thanks to your efforts,\n{player_name}.
Oh, goodness.\nI haven't done anything special.

You say that, but I don't think there'd be
anywhere near this many different folks
running around the Halidom if you weren't
the boss.
I don't know about that... Well, whatever\nthe reason, so long as everyone's happy,\nI'm happy, too.
So, how did we come to talk about this?
Oh, Grimnir seemed to be struck by the\ndiversity of the Halidom's residents.
Did you have some question or concern\nabout that, Grimnir?
When divergent forms and faiths collide, it\noft beckons a maelstrom at best. At worst,\nit portends a singularity of fates.
Still no idea what you're talking about.
Ugh. I'm saying it can be tricky when lots\nof different people come together.
Your mana makes it clear you are not\nhuman.
What am I? Well, if you would know...
I am the wind that blows through time. The\nTuner who imposes order upon a world\nin chaos. I am the mad cyclone, Griiim—
Wha—hey! Nooo, I was just getting to the\nbest bit!
I'm starting to think we don't know who you\nare precisely because you always dodge\nthe question with your abstruse bloviation.
Yeah, all your abstruse bloviation!\n...Remind me what that means again?
Er, something abstruse is inaccessible and\ndifficult to understand. And to bloviate is\nto speak a lot yet say very little, I believe?
To say very—HEY! That's not fair at all!\nI work really hard to think these lines up!
Then tell us, plainly. I struggle to think\nthat you're secretly a villain, but I cannot\ntrust someone I know nothing about.
I'm sorry. But know that I am not your\nenemy. I hope you can trust in that, at\nleast.
Are you sure that's wise? That means\ngranting free run of the Halidom to an\nunknown entity.
He must have circumstances he's not at\nliberty to share. In the time I've known\nhim, Grimnir has proven trustworthy.
Who or whatever he is, I believe that is\nreason enough to grant him a place here.\nDo you object?
*sigh* I don't know what to do with you\nsometimes... And yet, I'm not surprised\nin the slightest by your verdict.
If the castle's master welcomes him, he's\nas much a part of the Halidom as I am.
I should think I've said nothing to merit\nthanks.
Let me thank you as well, Prince. It was an\ninevitability of fate that we should meet.\nFor ours is a destined alliance.
Know that my winds shall never pierce the\nflesh of my allies. I swear before you now\nthat they shall be ever as your shield!
Cool story, bro. Whatever you say.
I...feel like you guys' reactions are getting\nweaker over time here.
(The prince is kind of heart and commands\nthe trust of all who dwell here. I cannot\nimagine he would disrupt fate's flow...)
(But the keeper told me that he was an\nirregularity who had no equal counterpart\nin any of the other timelines.)
(Just what does that mean for this world?\nFor all worlds, across all realities?)
(Even fate's keeper held no answer to that\nquestion.)
Determining that is my task as Tuner.
